📌 Quick Guide for a Cool CapCut Effect 

1. Record Two Videos:
↳ Point at the wall like you're checking a list.
↳ Write a to-do list in your notes and screen record checking it off.
2. Add Videos to CapCut:
↳ Import both videos.
↳ Place the list video as an overlay.
3. Resize and Splice:
↳ Resize the list video to show only the list.
↳ Choose "Splice" and click "Darken."
4. Align and Animate:
↳ Match the overlay with your pointing action.
↳ Add the "Drop Down" animation.
5. Duplicate and Remove Background:
↳ Duplicate the overlay, put it below, and remove the background.

Done! You've made a cool effect!

🤍 SAVE THIS REEL for later 🤍
Some of my favorite visual hooks for content videos on socials!

✅ POV walking
✅ Stirring coffee
✅ Zoom out
✅ View with a curtain
✅ Putting glasses on the book
✅ Showing a desk w/ rotation

🤍 BONUS 🤍
💫 Use my free videos and use these hooks for this week!

Day 1. How I make XYZ in only x minutes/days/hours
Ex) How I make $5k in only 3 hours without showing my face.

Day 2. POV: you got [insert result] when you stopped worrying about ___ & started ___ instead
Ex) POV: You gained 10k followers when you stopped worrying about the algorithm & started posting authentically instead

Day 3. If you want [insert desire], then try this
Ex) If you want consistent monthly revenue, then try this

Day 4. Tired of ____? Here’s how to fix it.
Ex) Tired of getting low engagement on your posts? Here’s how to fix it.

Day 5. X years ago, I was ____. Now I’m ____. Here’s how I did it.
Ex) 2 years ago, I had 500 followers. Now I’m a full-time content creator. Here’s how I did it.

Day 6. Ever wondered how you can ____ in just one?
Ex) Ever wondered how you can batch-create a month’s content in just one day?

Day 7. Biggest mistakes you’re making with ____.
Ex) Biggest mistakes you’re making with your pricing strategy.

📌 THIS IS MY GUIDE FOR YOU 

💬 Comment ‘GROW’ to get my FREE trainings and guide how I gained 124k followers in 9 months & built 6 figure business 🫶

How I grew from 0-124k followers less than a year?

MY EXTRA BONUS GUIDE HERE 👇

🤳 REELS:
➪ Post 3-4 reels per week (focus on sharable metric: educative, relatable, problem-solving content)
➪ B-roll: 5-8 seconds / tutorial with voice over:15-45second / talking to camera: 40-1:30
➪ Use ai caption using CapCut when you talk to camera
➪ Use a strong text hook/title with fast zoom out effect
➪ Take a break every Sunday

🎞️ CAROUSEL/SINGLE POSTS:
➪ Create 1-2 static posts per week
➪ Stop using text-heavy graphic - less is more! 
➪ Add value each slide with eye catchy graphics
➪ Add a clear call to actions at the end of slide
➪ Add alt text using your laptop 

☕️ STORIES:
➪ 80/20 rule: Talk about your business 80% and personal thing 20%
➪ Take a break every Sunday
➪ Use a poll sticker every morning on Monday (after taking 24 hours break)
➪ Add 5 relevant hashtags and hide it 

🫶 Send to someone who would like to grow Instagram!
🤍 Save this so that you can grow IG faster this year

Super easy slow rotation tutorial to spice up your edits 🎥 

This rotation editing is one of my favorites, and my reel with 7M views uses a slow rotation.

📌 STEP-BY-STEP HERE  ⤵️
1. Open CapCut 
2. Select your clip
3. Add your keyframe where you want the rotation to start
4. Scroll to the end of the clip & rotate + zoom at the same time
5. Keyframe will automatically be added 
6. Once you’re happy with the effect, tap on the "Export" button at the top-right corner of the screen.

📌 How you can use this technique:
↳  The rotate zoom-in effect looks cool and can make your videos pop. Use it to highlight important parts of your reel. This will catch viewers’ attention and keep them watching.
↳  Show a new product, begin with a close-up shot and slowly zoom out while rotating the camera.

🫶 Share this to someone who wants to spice up their reel to increase reel views!

caption.text:
👉 Today, I am not giving you the ULTIMATE framework on how to grow Instagram faster..

INSTEAD, I want to tell you that Mindset shift is more important than any formula or framework.

It’s been almost one year since I started Instagram business. It’s been an amazing journey with you.

📍 During this time, I’ve made some changes but the key changes are:
〰️ Move from SMM to selling my own digital courses
〰️ Grow my account by 125k followers
〰️ Make 5x more than my previous income
〰️ Got multiple M views organically

🔔 Success isn't a quick race….it's a journey. Don't rush it! Instead of worrying about how fast you can make your business successful, focus on becoming the kind of person who's ready to work hard and keep going.

💪 To succeed in business, we need to grow and change. It's like learning and getting stronger. It takes time and effort. 

Every challenge we face and every lesson we learn is like a brick we use to build our success.

So, enjoy the ride, and remember that it's not about how fast you go. It's about how much you learn and grow. 

Be proud of every step you take, and you'll be on your way to a great business and a great life. 🌱💼

🫶 Share this to someone who needs this reminder!

🥂 Want to learn exactly how I create and build own empire and be own boss? 
💬 Comment ‘CLUB’ then I’ll send you a link to join TCCM so that you can start creating content that will help you fulfill your dreams 🤍

Want to learn How I exactly achieved? 👩‍💻

📢 Comment "REEL" to get my FREE IG Viral Reel Checklists (I always check this criteria) & Viral training videos.

📍My exact strategy here 

1️⃣ HOOK - All my reels with M views share a common factor: I used the 'timelapse' editing technique and synced my text hooks to music with social proof results.
People pay more attention to data, proof, and number things.
e.g: I started ___ [insert your business niche] business 3 months ago and here’s what happened & show the result in reel > this makes people curious how to achieve these outcome.

2️⃣ CAPTION FORMULA - Sell more with my IG Caption formula
Caption hook
〰️ Grab their attention by using question or a strong hook
✍🏻 Educate (body)
〰️ Provide value in easily digestible chunks
〰️ Use either 4-5 emojis or number
〰️ Fake it until you make it - remember you’re an expert and use simplified word and authority tone
📣 CTAS with a reason
〰️ Get your audience to engage and take next step
〰️ Lead them to your offerings to buy using ManyChat (AI)
💎 Relevant Keywords 
〰️ I found this helpful rather than hashtags
〰️ Use 8-10 SEO keywords / go check your competitors what kind of keywords do they use

IG Algorithm does not care about
↳ Not Save ❌
↳ Not Like ❌

☕️ INSTEAD!
Focus on Sends per Reach Ratio: Prioritize creating content that encourages sharing among friends, as this metric is crucial for increasing visibility and engagement according to Instagram's CEO.
📌 SHARE = 400 views
Create shareable content such as entertaining, newsworthy, or informative content.

⌚️ Block your time to focus on researching content, or block the entire day (I usually prepare my content a couple of days in advance), so you don't have to be perfect like with a monthly or weekly plan. Sometimes creativity comes from going with the flow.
The key is to stick to your goal or plan but be creative freely when it comes to creating content.

〰️ Are you still feeling lost what to do to grow your Instagram?

caption.text:
🪄 Make your images stand out with a crisp white line.

I got asked many times how to create the aesthetic outlined carouse post! 
It‘s perfect for social media posts, presentations, and any creative project that needs a little something extra. 

STEP-BY-STEP HERE ⬇️

1. Open Canva: Go to Canva and select your image.
2. Duplicate the Image: Click on the image and duplicate it.
3. Select the Second Layer: Click on the duplicated image.
4. Remove Background: Go to ‘EFFECT’ and click ‘BG Remover’.
5. Add Shadow: Click on ‘SHADOW’ and select ‘Outline’.
6. Adjust Size: Set the size to 10.
7. Align Images: Make sure both images are lined up.
8. Change Outline Color: Change the outline color to white.
Now you’re ready to create a more stylish design!

👯‍♀️ Share this to someone who wants to make their images pop!

💭 Comment ‘ME’ then I’ll share my sample of outline effect aesthetic design canva link for FREE so that you can practice by looking at my examples!

👩‍💻 4 ways to optimize reel so that you increase your reel views!

1. Optimize IG & Camera settings 🤳
Iphone Camera settings:
↳ Shoot in 1080 at 60 fps
↳ Turn on ‘Enhanced Stabilization’
↳ Turn off ‘HDR video (High-Efficiency)’
↳ Go to ‘Format’ > ‘Most Compatible’
IG setting:
↳ IG setting - turn on ‘allow high-quality uploads’

2. Know the Purpose of Your Reel ☕️
Before you hit record, think about what your reel will focus on:
↳ Is it educational? (e.g., sharing a quick tutorial on graphic design)
↳ Are you showcasing a special event or offer? (e.g., announcing a limited-time discount on your courses)
↳ Will you include behind-the-scenes (BTS) footage? (e.g., showing your workspace or creative process)
↳ Consider the tone. Should it be funny, serious, or inspiring?

3. Stay on beat! - upgrade your editing skill 🎧
Practice makes perfect! I keep testing and testing until it looks great in sync with the music. 
↳ I use CapCut to edit my reel and then use IG native fonts. 
↳ Check out trending reels to see how they sync with the beat and try to match that style!

4. Write Catchy Captions ✍🏻
A great hook will draw people in, but make sure your caption keeps them engaged! Use a strategy to craft captions that connect with your audience.
Don't worry! 🫶 I got the answer for you 
📌 I offer 25 caption prompts each month to make your posting easier. Just plug in your ideas and start sharing!

💬 Comment 'CLUB' to grab new go-to resource with a monthly content formula that helps you make your content dream a reality! Including my FREE winning caption formula!

🥂Share this to someone who wants to increase reel views!
